article.headline: Brown 95, Hartford 82
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Mark McAndrew scored 30 points and Damon Huffman added 22 as Brown University defeated the University of Hartford, 95-82, on Friday. McAndrew was 6-of-10 on 3-point shots and a perfect 10-of-10 from the free throw line to lead Brown (4-7). Brown hit a season-high 16 3-point shots in 28 attempts (57.1 per cent). The Bears made 14 3-point shots during a 72-68 loss to Rhode Island on Dec. 5. Nathan Eads (13 points) and Scott Friske (11 points) also reached double figures for Brown. Bo Taylor led Hartford (6-5) with 19 points while Joe Zeglinski added 18 and Jaret Von Rosenberg scored 16. Brown never trailed, building a 28-11 lead midway through the first half after a 13-0 run. McAndrew scored eight points during the run, including two 3-point shots. McAndrew had 19 points in the first half, which ended with Brown leading 38-24. Huffman hit four 3-point shots early in the second half as Brown built their biggest lead of the game, 72-47, with 7:28 remaining. Zeglinski hit his fourth 3-point shot with 1:57 left in regulation as Hartford pulled within 84-74. But McAndrew converted 4-of-4 from the free throw line to clinch the victory.
